843. ego quidem hercle. ‘I indeed. to tell you the truth, father, the thing vexes me.’ This literal construe will shew that there is here an anacoluthon. The sentence begins with ego in the nom. as is a verb, such as aegre patior, were to follow to which ego would be subject. But instead of such a verb the sentence finishes with ca res me male habet so that ego is lest ‘pendent.’ See Madvig L. G. 480. In comedy such broken construction is not un- common, especially if the subject is a delicate one, e.g. Pseud. 2 ff.
